    <name>
				<text>7.4.5.1 Exercise: Inverse of a 2 x 2 matrix (NOT IN QUIZ)</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Find the inverses of the following matrices</p>
<p>\(\bf A={@A@}\), \(\bf B={@B@}\), \(\bf C={@C@}\).</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
    <li>
        <div>\(\bf A^{-1}=\) [[input:ans1]][[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</div>
    </li>
    <li>
        <div>\(\bf B^{-1}=\) [[input:ans2]][[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</div>
    </li>
    <li>
        <div>\(\bf C^{-1}=\) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]</div>
    </li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p></p>
<p></p>
<p><b>FEEDBACK</b></p>
<p><b></b></p>The inverse of a 2 \(\times\) 2 matrix \[{@matrixabcd@}\] is \[\frac{1}{ad-bc}{@matrixdbca@}.\]<br>
<p>Therefore the inverse of matrix \[\bf A = {@A@}\] is</p>
<p>\[\bf A^{-1} = \frac{1}{({@A[1,1]@}).({@A[2,2]@}) -({@A[1,2]@}).({@A[2,1]@})}{@ta1@} = \frac{1}{({@A[1,1]*A[2,2]@}) -({@A[1,2]*A[2,1]@})}{@ta1@} ={@ta1@}.\]</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>The inverse of matrices \( \bf B\) and \( \bf C\) can be found similarly and are</p>
<p>\[ B^{-1} = {@ta2@} \quad C^{-1} = {@ta3@}.\]</p>
<p></p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
